This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new optimization algorithm for deep network architectures. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with optimization algorithms for neural networks. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is often used in these fields. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) as natural gradient descent is a technique used in natural language processing.
